# No Manual Memoization (React Compiler)

This project uses **React Compiler**, which automatically memoizes components and values.
**Never** use `useCallback`, `useMemo`, or `React.memo` — the compiler does it for you.

## Forbidden

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — unnecessary, React Compiler handles this
const handleClick = useCallback(() => { ... }, [dep]);
const computed = useMemo(() => expensiveCalc(a, b), [a, b]);
export default React.memo(MyComponent);
```

## Correct

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — plain functions and values, compiler optimizes automatically
const handleClick = () => { ... };
const computed = expensiveCalc(a, b);
export default MyComponent;
```

## Applies to

- All hooks (`useCallback`, `useMemo`)
- `React.memo` wrapper
- Any manual memoization pattern
